.TH "tty_mode_ioctl" 9 "tty_mode_ioctl" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
tty_mode_ioctl \- mode related ioctls
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" tty_mode_ioctl
.BI "(struct tty_struct *tty "  ","
.BI "struct file *file "  ","
.BI "unsigned int cmd "  ","
.BI "unsigned long arg "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "tty" 12
tty for the ioctl
.IP "file" 12
file pointer for the tty
.IP "cmd" 12
command
.IP "arg" 12
ioctl argument

Perform non line discipline specific mode control ioctls. This
is designed to be called by line disciplines to ensure they provide
consistent mode setting.
